    "https://timewarpboulder.com": {
      "product": {
        "id": 8002392686710,
        "title": "Prez 1973 #1 - 2.5 - $3.75",
        "handle": "prez-1973-1-2-5-3-75",
        "body_html": "<p>Boss Smiley attempts to find a candidate that will be his puppet, but Prez, with Eagle Free's help declares his independence.</p><p><b>Copyright ? 1973 by National Periodical Publications, Inc.\r\n\r\nOn-sale date from Comic Reader #96.</b></p><ul>\n<li>Gain weight! - Inside front cover ad for body building course.</li>\n<li>Peter Revson Drives This Car - Ad for Aurora AFX Model Motoring toys.\r\nBetween page 4 and 5 of previous story.</li>\n<li>The Score-Boards Don't Tell All! - House ad for Champion Sports #1.\r\nTop of page between page 4 and 5 of previous story.</li>\n<li> - ad for subscriptions to various DC comics.\r\nBottom of page between page 4 and 5 of previous story.</li>\n<li>The Day Bill Told Off His Boss - Ad for Cleveland Institute of Electronics, Inc. told in photo story strip.\r\nBetween page 9 and 10 of previous story.</li>\n<li> - Ad for toys and novelties.\r\nBetween page 11 and 12 of previous story.</li>\n<li>Task Force / Cannon Ball - Ad for two war games, Task Force and Cannon Ball, with toy figures, from Helen of Toy, Co.\r\nBetween page 16 and 17 of previous story.</li>\n<li>Super Bodybuilding Course - Ad for body building course.\r\nBetween page 22 and 23 of previous story.</li>\n<li>Tank Trap / Fighting Ships - Ad for two games from Helen of Toy, Co.</li>\n<li> - Ad for correspondence school.</li>\n<li>Are You Ready for a Daisy B-B Gun. - Ad for Daisy B-B Guns, inviting you to send away for a free copy of ?The Air Rifle Marksman? booklet by Daisy. Color ad on inside back cover.</li>\n<li>Do You Need Extra Money? - Cheerful House. Back cover ad seeking sellers of greeting cards.</li>\n</ul>",
